featured_reviews.review_id:
Asalaam Alaikum
Amazed to find a Masjid at this location...had searched on the internet before leaving for Dharmasala...found it with the help of local people, they were very helpful to guide..
It's a very small Masjid as not much of local muslim population...more of migrants from neighbouring states...offered my Zuhr namaz (sadly not with jamaat...missed the opportunity)...loved the experience. Can say that its maintained well with very few people to manage.
Its a bit difficult to locate...just as you reach the petrol pump you have to go a bit upwards and ask local people to guide you...there's a small paan shop besides which there are narrow steps going down...just follow it also has a separate section for women.
Do visit this Masjid brethren
JAZAKALLAH KHAIR

featured_reviews.review_id: Walked for 4 hours from Heini village to this ancient mosque that is hidden deep in Dharamsala . I met the Imam and the Khadim of the Masjid and they offered me tea and biscuits and we chatted for a while . The structure of the Masjid is relatively small and it is surrounded by a market . However, I truly felt at home in this humble place of worship.
